Fig. 13
). Buccal tube width: internal 1.0 [
3.4
], external 2.0 [ 7.0 ] with one bend in posterior part of tube (visible only in lateral view). Stylet supports inserted on buccal tube at 16.5 [ 56.0 ]. Pharyngeal bulb slightly oval with apophyses and two macroplacoids (
Fig. 13
). Microplacoid and septula absent. Pharyngeal apophyses very large (almost as large as macroplacoids) and triangular in shape. Macroplacoids slightly oval, without constrictions. First macroplacoid 3.0 [
10.2
] long. Second macroplacoid shorter, 2.0 [ 7.0 ] long. Macroplacoid row 6.0 [
20.3
] long.

